Justin Bronk warned that Russia is in a "dangerous position" as troops meet a strong and unexpected Ukrainian resistance. He laid out three options, the first being driving troops from Melitopol to Dnipro to meet more troops before advancing to Kharkiv. The second is continuing attacks on major cities and the third involves an attempt to encircle Mykolaiv.It comes after the British Defence Ministry said the invasion has "largely stalled on all fronts" with Russia suffering "heavy losses". FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES...